category: MUSICAL INSTRUMENTS
category comment: 

clue: A modification of a Portuguese guitar, it became popular in Hawaii in the late 19th century

response: ukulele

clue: The double-action type of this instrument has 2 reeds tuned to the same note for extra fun when using the bellows

response: an accordion

clue: Ben Franklin made a "glass" type of this instrument, totally different from the "mouth organ" type

response: a harmonica

clue: The Greek for "wood" gives us the name of this instrument that's struck with padded mallets

response: xylophone

clue: Also known as an etherophone, this boxy electronic instrument was used by The Beach Boys

response: a theremin

